Traininglist<- createDataPartition(y=Student$grade,p=.80,list=FALSE)
Training<-Student[Traininglist,]
Test<-Student[-Traininglist,]
#testing tree model
Ttree<- train(grade~netflix_hours+social_media_hours+study_hours_per_day+mental_health_rating, data = Training,method="treebag")
tree<- rpart(grade~netflix_hours+social_media_hours+study_hours_per_day+mental_health_rating,data=Student)
prp(tree)

predOut<- predict(Ttree,newdata =Test )
confusion<- confusionMatrix(predOut, Test$grade)
confusion

SG<- ggplot(Student)+ geom_point(aes(x=studyhourspersleephour, y= exam_score))
SG

SG1 <- SG+ geom_smooth(method = "lm",aes(x=studyhourspersleephour,y=exam_score))+ ggtitle("study to sleep relationships on exam score")
SG1
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

#Function of predictive modeling
mystudypersleep<- function(study,sleep){
  x<-study/sleep
  y<-(41.9531*x)+45.6430
  y
  z<-SG1+geom_point(aes(x=x,y=y),colour="green",size = 5)+geom_label(aes(x=x,y=y),label=y,nudge_x = 0.25,nudge_y = 0.1)
  z
}
mystudypersleep(5,9)
